<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      input:required {
         background: lightgrey;
         color: red;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> The <b>:required</b> CSS pseudo-class represents any form element that has the <b>required</b> attribute set on it. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   
   <form action="#">
      <label>
         * First Name: <input type="text" name="first-name" required />
      </label>
      <br />
      <label>
         * Last Name: <input type="text" name="last-name" required />
      </label>
      <br />
      <label>
         Age: <input type="number" name="age" />
      </label>
   </form>
</body>
</html>